  "text": "The Kafka producer `acks` configuration propagates through 9 key files across the client and broker codebases:\n\n1. **ProducerConfig.java** (line 123): Defines `ACKS_CONFIG = \"acks\"` as a public static constant with allowed values \"all\", \"-1\", \"0\", \"1\" (line 383-388). The `parseAcks()` method (line 639) normalizes \"all\" to \"-1\". The `postProcessAndValidateIdempotenceConfigs()` method (line 577) validates acks consistency with idempotence settings.\n\n2. **KafkaProducer.java** (line 526): The `newSender()` method reads the acks config as `Short.parseShort(producerConfig.getString(ProducerConfig.ACKS_CONFIG))` and passes it to the Sender constructor.\n\n3. **Sender.java** (lines 99, 134, 148): Stores acks as `private final short acks`. In `sendProduceRequest()` (line 864), the acks value is encoded into the wire protocol via `new ProduceRequestData().setAcks(acks)` (line 899). The `sendProduceRequests()` method (line 856-858) distributes per-broker batches with the same acks value.\n\n4. **ProduceRequest.java** (lines 91, 101-107, 193-195): Wraps the protocol data; constructor copies `this.acks = data.acks()`. Exposes `acks()` accessor. Uses acks==0 to suppress error responses (line 166).\n\n5. **ProduceRequest.json** (line 55): Protocol schema defines `Acks` as `int16` field at versions 0+.\n\n6. **KafkaApis.scala** (line 537): Broker-side `handleProduceRequest` extracts `produceRequest.acks` and passes as `requiredAcks` to `replicaManager.handleProduceAppend()`. Also uses acks==0 for response handling (line 499).\n\n7. **ReplicaManager.scala** (lines 674-712): `appendRecords()` validates via `isValidRequiredAcks()` (line 683) which accepts only -1, 0, or 1 (line 1363-1365). If requiredAcks==-1, creates DelayedProduce for ISR-aware waiting (line 1358).\n\n8. **Partition.scala** (lines 1361-1388): `appendRecordsToLeader()` checks `requiredAcks == -1` to enforce min.isr: if ISR size < min.isr and acks==-1, throws NotEnoughReplicasException (line 1370). Also `checkEnoughReplicasReachOffset()` (line 1089) is called when requiredAcks==-1 to verify all ISR replicas have caught up.\n\n9. **DelayedProduce.scala** (lines 43-47, 57-61): `ProduceMetadata` case class carries `produceRequiredAcks: Short`. The `DelayedProduce` operation waits for ISR replicas to reach the produce offset before completing the request.",
